In Object Oriented Programming, we have to think in terms of objects. This is, we have to think of the object that compose our problem. 

In each object we can identify, we will have
* data (type, color, position, etc.) atributos adverbios
* actions or behaviour (walk(), run(), hike(), etc.) verbos

1. Computadora
Atributos: Monitor, botones, entrada de puerto USB, Tamaño, Cámara
Acciones: prender, apagar, suspender, subir, bajar 


Paradigmas de programación 
1. Programación Estructurada
2. Programación Orientada a Objetos (POO o OOP) 
3. Programación Funcional (Scala, Haskell)
	f(x) = x + 3
	g(x) = (f(x)) + 8
4. Programación Orientada a negocios (COBOL)
5. Programación ...

